What is the difference between inline, internal, and external CSS? Which is most common in production?
Inline CSS is written inside the element, Interal CSS is written inside the <style> External CSS is from an external source like a seperate file. 
We can use inline css for single element, internal CSS for a group of elements and external CSS for multiple Pages

The most common one in production is external CSS.


