What is an iframe? Why does it create challenges for test automation?
An iframe (inline frame) is an HTML element (<iframe>) used to embed another webpage inside the current webpage.
It creates issues with automation because it has a seperate DOM structure. we need to explicitly switch to the iframe. This may have multiple issues like, embedded iframe may have a complex dom structure, or there might be restrictions on the iframe
or there might be loading issues.










